Package org.spongepowered.api.data.manipulators.items

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BlockItemData
    Represents data about a block being represented by this item data.
    BreakableData
    Represents an editable collection of BlockTypes that can be broken with this item.
    CloneableData
    Represents an item that can be cloned or copied.
    CoalItemData
    Represents the coal item that can define the type of coal it is.
    CookedFishItemData
    Represents the type of CookedFish the cooked fish item is.
    DurabilityData
    Represents an item that has limited number of uses.
    EnchantmentData
    Represents item data related to an item having active Enchantments.
    FishData
    Represents the type of Fish the fish item is.
    GoldenAppleItemData
    Represents the type of GoldenApple the golden apple item is.
    InventoryItemData
    Represents an item that can have an inventory.
    LoreData
    Lore is a list of Texts that are displayed on an item tooltip that can say anything and everything.
    MapItemData
    Represents map information to show a graphical map.
    PagedData
    Represents an item that has pages, like a book.
    PlaceableData
    Represents an item that can restrict the placement of itself to the defined block types.
    SpawnableData
    Represents an item that can spawn entities of a particular EntityType on use.
    StoredEnchantmentData
    Represents stored enchantments that can be used to apply the stored Enchantments on to another item stack.
